title: Aaron Carter, Singer, Dies at 34
description: Mr. Carter, who released his first album at age 9 and “Aaron’s Party” at age 12, was the younger brother of Nick Carter, a member of the Backstreet Boys.
dc:creator: Melina Delkic and McKenna Oxenden

media:content.media:description: Aaron Carter in 2012. He released five studio albums and was a contestant on the show “Dancing With the Stars.”
